      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure it\u0027s a good idea. Either:\n- Use a sync chan, so that Go\u0027s native \"write-to-destination\" can be used\n- Use a locked slice, which is more risky\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dKBZlN0izeiY is a good overview of the performance trade offs.\n\nEither way, I don\u0027t think it is a significant performance implication, since this code is not CPU bound, so whatever. :)",
      "revId": "454e04501d6e5e5ce7fe4e8e43d4dfc79f6af7eb",
